'''Balázs Orbán''' (1829–1890) was a [[Magyars|Hungarian]] writer, historian and politician.

He was born in Lengyelfalva, [[Grand Principality of Transylvania]] (today [[Polonița]], [[Romania]]) and died in [[Budapest]].
His most important work is "''Székelyföld leírása''", an encyclopedic description of the [[Szekely Land]], first published in 1868 in [[Budapest, Hungary]].

