{{Infobox Politician | name = Elbert Roest | image = Elbert-roest.jpg | caption = | office = Mayor of [[Laren, North Holland]] | term_start = 2002 | term_end = | predecessor = [[Theo Hendriks (mayor)|Theo Hendriks]] | successor = | office1 = Alderman of [[Doesburg]] | term_start1 = 1992 | term_end1 = 2002 | predecessor1= | successor1 = | office2 = Municipal councillor of Doesburg | term_start2 = 1992 | term_end2 = 2002 | predecessor2= | successor2 = | birth_date = {{Birth date|1954|10|13|df=yes}} | birth_place = [[Hoogezand]], Netherlands | death_date = | death_place = | party = [[Democrats 66]] }}
'''Elbert Jan Roest''' (born 13 October 1954 in [[Hoogezand]]) is a Dutch historian, politician and former teacher. He is a member of [[Democrats 66]] (D66).
From 1992 to 2002, Roest was a member of the municipal council of [[Doesburg]] and also an alderman. Since 2002, he has been mayor of [[Laren, North Holland]].
Roest studied history at the [[University of Groningen]].
